<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-08-11T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-08-11T04:00:00-05:00" n="406" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d406">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/9290: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Hankow</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Josselyn</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Hankow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-11T17:00:00+08:00">August 11, 1937—5
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received August 11—1:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>My August 11, 11 a.m.<note n="79" xml:id="d406fn79">Not
                                    printed.</note> A Japanese naval vessel is leaving this
                                afternoon for Shanghai carrying all remaining Japanese. The Chinese
                                population of the Japanese Concession which had all previously
                                evacuated will now be permitted to return.</p>
                            <p>Repeated to Nanking, Peiping and Shanghai.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Josselyn</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>